**:<small>[[Computer programming/Structured programming|Structured]] ~ [[Computer programming/Imperative programming|Imperative]] ~ [[Computer programming/Procedural programming|Procedural]] ~ [[Computer programming/Object oriented programming|Object oriented]] ~ [[Computer programming/Generic programming|Generic ]]<ref>[http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-TTL.html Ada Reference Manual, ISO/IEC 8652:2005(E) Ed. 3], [http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-12.html Section 12: Generic Units]</ref> ~ [[Computer programming/Concurrent programming|Concurrent]]<ref>[http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-TTL.html Ada Reference Manual, ISO/IEC 8652:2005(E) Ed. 3], [http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-E.html Annex E: Distributed Systems]</ref> ~ [[Computer programming/Distributed programming|Distributed]]<ref>[http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-TTL.html Ada Reference Manual, ISO/IEC 8652:2005(E) Ed. 3], [http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-9.html Section 9: Tasks and Synchronization]</ref> ~ [[Computer programming/System Programming|System]]<ref>[http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-TTL.html Ada Reference Manual, ISO/IEC 8652:2005(E) Ed. 3], [http://www.adaic.org/standards/05rm/html/RM-C.html Annex C: Systems Programming]</ref> ~ [[Computer programming/Embedded Programming|Embedded]]</small>
**:Ada is a structured language with a [[Programming:Pascal|Pascal]] like syntax which may make Ada a suitable teaching language.  The Wikibook for Ada is the only Wikibook which has an entry for all [[Computer_programming#Key_concepts|Key concepts]]. Apart from academic use<ref>[http://www.adacore.com/academic_overview.php The GNAT Academic Program (GAP)]</ref>, Ada is professionally used<ref>[http://www.adacore.com/aa_lookwho.php Look Who's Using Ada]</ref> in Air Traffic Control, Aviation <small>(Commercial and Defense)</small>, Rail Transportation, Communications <small>(Satellites and Receivers)</small> and Swiss banks - most of which are constantly on the lookout for good Ada programmers.
