: Initially, Pascal was a hypothetical language intended to teach students structured programming, and generations of students have "cut their teeth" on Pascal as an introductory language in undergraduate courses. Pascal was developed by [[w:Niklaus Wirth|Niklaus Wirth]], who also developed Modula and Oberon as more real-world languages. Variants of Pascal are still widely used today, both in education and software development.
